Def:-
REST APIs is a popular way to build scalable and maintainable backend services. 
REST (Representational State Transfer) is an architectural style,
or design pattern for building networked applications, specifically web services. that can be easily consumed by clients. 

REST (Representational State Transfer):-
A widely used web API architecture, That operates over HTTP And uses URLs for resource identifications.
It primarily relies on standard HTTP methods. like:GET, POST, PUT & DELETE / CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations.
Ex: Fetching data from a REST API
    fetch('https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users')
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(data => console.log(data))
    .catch(error => console.log('Error:', error));

HTTP Methods and REST
  GET: Retrieve data (Read).
  POST: Create new data (Create).
  PUT/PATCH: Update existing data (Update).
  DELETE: Remove data (Delete).

1/ Setting up the environment
    mkdir my-rest-api
    cd my-rest-api
    npm init -y

2/ Install Dependencies
   The following packages are commonly used in a REST API:
      Express: is a minimal and flexible web framework for Node.js.
      Mongoose: If you're using MongoDB for your database.
      Cors: To allow Cross-Origin Resource Sharing, enabling our API to be used from different origins.

